<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-14"><hi rend="italic">April 14,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 224.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt this morning at 7 o’clock of Department dispatch in cipher,
                            which I translate as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>, <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1898.</hi></p>
                                <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister., Madrid:</hi></p>
                                <p>In case of war, where there is real danger to American citizens
                                    who can not provide means of transportation, you and consuls
                                    will provide for passage and draw on Department.</p>
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I give the necessary instruction to-day to Consul-General Bowen at
                            Barcelona, and request him to notify consuls.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>